    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-26T04:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-26T04:30:00-05:00" n="24"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/2</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé d’Affaires in Russia</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_WCS1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-26T12:00:00+02:30">
                        <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1914, noon</hi>.</date>
                </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Diplomatic and political circles here consider situation most serious and Russian
                    intervention inevitable in case of Austro-Servian conflict. Ministry held a
                    conference last night and issued official <hi rend="italic">communiqué</hi>
                    stating that the Russian Government is greatly disturbed by Austro [-Servian]
                    conflict, situation to which it cannot remain indifferent. Ministers have been
                    summoned by the Emperor.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WCS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
